---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title="About | Yujin Ok" description="My story — from South Korea to Melbourne, fitness instructor to developer." />
		<style>
			main {
				max-width: 800px;
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding: 2em 1em;
			}
			.section {
				display: flex;
				gap: 2em;
				align-items: flex-start;
				margin-bottom: 4em;
			}
			.section.reverse {
				flex-direction: row-reverse;
			}
			.section img {
				width: 300px;
				height: 400px;
				object-fit: cover;
				border-radius: 8px;
				flex-shrink: 0;
			}
			.section-text h2 {
				font-size: 1.8rem;
				margin-bottom: 0.5em;
			}
			.section-text p {
				line-height: 1.8;
				color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
			}
			hr {
				margin: 2em 0;
				border: none;
				border-top: 1px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
			}
			@media (max-width: 640px) {
				.section, .section.reverse {
					flex-direction: column;
				}
				.section img {
					width: 100%;
					height: 300px;
				}
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>About Me</h1>
			<hr />

			<div class="section">
				<img src="/img/psy.jpg" alt="Yujin" />
				<div class="section-text">
					<h2>My journey started from...</h2>
					<p>
						I am originally from South Korea, but I have travelled to several places and have been
						living in Melbourne, Australia for 8 years.
					</p>
					<p>
						I came to Australia with one backpack and a two-month travelling plan with the intention
						of learning more about fitness instructing, as I was already a fitness instructor in
						Korea. But quickly, I fell so in love with this city that I never went back home.
					</p>
					<p>
						I have previously travelled across 11 different states in America on a 6-week road trip
						and have also visited Sydney, Brisbane and the Sunshine Coast in Queensland. I also took
						a cruise to Fukuoka, Japan — Gangnam Style was hitting the world back then so I did a
						lot of that horse dancing with Japanese strangers! And I rode a motorcycle through Baja,
						Mexico. Rough on the body, lifetime experience.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<hr />

			<div class="section reverse">
				<img src="/img/dance2.jpg" alt="Yujin dancing" />
				<div class="section-text">
					<h2>My career in the past...</h2>
					<p>
						I have always loved dancing since I started being able to walk. I used to teach K-pop
						dance choreography back in Korea, and that interest developed further into fitness
						instructing. I have been instructing various classes at many different fitness facilities
						back home and here in Melbourne for 14 years.
					</p>
					<p>
						The combination of my passion for the movement of the human body and my interest in
						clinical knowledge drove me to go back to university in 2018 to study a Bachelor of
						Health Science, majoring in human anatomy and physiology.
					</p>
					<p>
						Upon completing my degree, I was offered a full-time job at a Haematology lab where I
						helped perform full blood tests and much more — pretty much whatever your doctor
						requests.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<hr />

			<div class="section">
				<img src="/img/lab2.jpg" alt="Lab work" />
				<div class="section-text">
					<h2>How I got into coding...</h2>
					<p>
						As the pandemic hit in 2020, just like many of you, I was stuck at home finishing my
						degree. I was also teaching dance fitness classes via Zoom to Koreans and my gym clients
						here. Some requested if I could pre-record the classes and make them available. So I
						attempted to make videos with the intention of using YouTube — but this later developed
						into an idea: "how can I make my own platform to put all my content where I can also
						make revenue?"
					</p>
					<p>
						I started teaching myself HTML and CSS through various online materials. This continued
						even after getting a full-time job. I also started noticing everyday problems around me
						— the lab software had inefficiencies that made my daily work harder, and I kept
						thinking about how I could fix them.
					</p>
					<p>
						Seeing these problems made my learning more engaging and personal. Leaving full-time
						work in the middle of a pandemic was one of the hardest decisions I've made, but I took
						the risk because I was too curious and really wanted to learn programming seriously.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
